# Cross-Stage Control Checklist

The following rules apply across all stages:

-   Do not treat the manifest as runtime truth.
-   Do not let Firebase Studio become the backend.
-   Do not expose raw repository URLs.
-   Do not implement launch behavior as frontend-only logic.
-   Do not skip route/surface separation.
-   Do not activate modules before their backend and launch contracts
    exist.
-   Do not allow payments, onboarding, or entitlements to be governed in
    browser state.
-   Do not clone all repos into the main workspace just because they are
    listed in the manifest.

