# Definition of Success

Stages 2--12 are successfully executed when:

-   the inner bench remains the validated backend runtime
-   the platform shell governs modules, launches, entitlements, and
    surfaces
-   Firebase Studio acts as a clean frontend layer over stable contracts
-   the manifest supports ecosystem awareness without repo bloat
-   external services are integrated through governed launch models
-   module activation is phased and controlled
-   billing, entitlement, and customer state remain platform-owned
-   security, audit, analytics, and operations are in place
-   staging/UAT proves the system works before go-live
